
This is a simple test suite. For each test <Name> there should be created an
executable under the name <Name>_app (rules to create it are in the Makefile
(which is generated by automake from Makefile.am)) and exist an "etalon"
output <Name>_app.ok and a script to run Test_<Name>. The scritpt could be
copied from one of existing scripts and renamed to proper name (or it could
be a separate script, if the things are not following standard scheme).



How to add a new standard test:

1) Write a test programm, <Name>_app.cpp (plus additional sources if necessary).

2) Copy one of existing test scripts to Test_<Name>, e.g.,
    cp Test_3DMatrix Test_<Name>

3) Adjust Makefile.am to reflect new executable. Usually, it is just adding
following strings to the next variables:
    Test_<Name>     ->      TESTS
    <Name>_app      ->      noinst_PROGRAMS
    <Name>_app.ok   ->      OKs
and writting rules for application:
    <Name>_app_SOURCES = <Name>_app.cpp

When modification of Makefile.am is finished, run autoreconf and ./configure
scripts in the project's root directory (say 'cd ../').

4) Create the test application, `make <Name_app>' and the etalon output,
`./<Name>_app > <Name>_app.ok'.

5) Check if it is running correctly, `make check'.


To use debug mode: set the environmental variable ISDEBUG. E.g.,
    ISDEBUG=YES make check



